Habitus. Body form weakly convex, subparallel (
Fig. 5
).

Female internal genitalia (
Fig. 9–10
). Gonocoxite 1 asetose (gc 1 ). Gonocoxite 2 falciform (gc 2 ), 1.6–1.8 times longer than its basal width, moderately curved, with medial basal ridge (mbr), and with medial (mes) and lateral (les) ensiform and apical nematiform (ns) setae. Shape of medial basal ridge and length of ensiform setae vary among species. Laterotergite (lt) with 8–11 setae. Spermatheca (sp) sclerotized, small, rufous, subparallel, either with enlarged basal half or almost spherical.
